@node faq6 "Frequent Questions: Bugs, known issues, and not yet implemented features"

@{b}Frequent Questions Part 6: Bugs, known issues, and not yet implemented features@{ub}

@{b}6.1. Bugs@{ub}
To see a list of open bugs and bugreports go to http://sourceforge.net/bugs/?group_id=2335


@{b}6.2. Known Issues@{ub}
Movement is sometimes jerky or slow.
We don't know what all the data in 'weapons.dat' and 'ammo.dat' means, so hit points
and damage don't work as well as in the original game. Sound effects in SI are sometimes
odd with the wave pack as some sounds were coded in Exult to correspond to the sfx
number in BG. This is a bug and will be addressed in due time.

In Fellowship meetings some NPCs appear not to attend these though they should and
sometimes even speak there. This is due to a bug in Exult which makes NPCs sit on
already taken seats and only the top most NPC can be seen. Moving the top most via
Hackmover makes the others visible.

If you run a resolution higher than the original (320x200) some NPCs that are further
away from the Avatar may seem to disappear and reappear when you get away or closer to them.

With scalers enabled you might encounter slow downs of the game. The team is working
on this right now and it is already a lot faster.

The speech in the intro is out of synch with the lips animations. But now it matches
the speed of the text.

There are reported problems with digital sound effects or speech when using Vortex series
sound cards under Win9x/ME. It's not sure if this is a driver or Exult issue.


@{b}6.3. Not yet implemented@{ub}
A few magic spells don't work yet.

